<div>		



<span class="section_title">2008 INTERNATIONAL CES   CONFERENCE PROGRAM   HIGHLIGHTS FULL   RANGE OF CONSUMER TECHNOLOGY</span>

	<br><br>
	<span class="subhead">More than 175  Conferences, Knowledge Track Sessions and Partner Programs Offered at the 2008 International CES </span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;9/25/2007</i></strong>
<br><br>
 The 2008 International CES<sup>&#174</sup> today announced its 

extensive lineup  of more than 175 conference sessions designed to help educate attendees on the  latest consumer electronics 

industry trends. The 2008 International CES, the  world&rsquo;s largest consumer technology tradeshow, will be held 

Monday-Thursday,  January 7-10 in Las Vegas, Nevada.
<p>
&ldquo;The International CES brings  together leading experts across the globe to deliver a wide range of  conferences and 

training sessions that cover all aspects of consumer  technology,&rdquo; said Karen Chupka,  senior vice president of events 

and conferences for the Consumer Electronics  Association (CEA)<sup>&#174</sup>, the producer of the International CES. 

&ldquo;CES is &nbsp;the top educational forum for consumer  technology and gives CES participants an unparalleled opportunity 

to learn from  and network with the best in the industry.&rdquo;
<p>
The diverse  program includes conference sessions on such hot product categories as digital  entertainment, wireless trends, 

audio, digital imaging, emerging technology,  gaming, home networking and in-vehicle technology.&nbsp; 
<p>
The 2008  International CES conference program consists of Knowledge Track sessions, Partner  Programs, and SuperSessions 

that cover virtually every aspect of business and  consumer technology in the world.
<p>
CES  Knowledge Tracks bring together experts to share their ideas and insight on a  variety of CE products and 

technologies.&nbsp;  Each track features in-depth content on specific market segments  including:
<p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Emerging  Technology</strong> &ndash; Innovation occurs so rapidly in the CE industry that keeping  up can 

leave you breathless. Get the critical information you need to  understand how the industry, markets and consumers will be 

affected by new and  improved technologies.</li>
  <li><strong>Home and  Lifestyle Entertainment</strong> &ndash; Consumers want their entertainment real, dynamic  and 

accessible. See what and how they&rsquo;ll be watching, listening and playing  from the comfort of their own homes.</li>
  <li><strong>In-Vehicle  Technology </strong>&ndash; See what drives this important category. Explore the amazing  advances 

in communications, security, navigation, safety and entertainment.</li>
  <li><strong>Issues and Attitudes </strong>&ndash; Explore a range of critical issues in  thought-provoking sessions on the 

hot-button topics of the day, including a  growing &ldquo;green&rdquo; consciousness in the industry and new sources of 

capital for  smaller innovators.<strong></strong></li>
  <li><strong>Just the  Facts: Research, Reports and Revelation </strong>&ndash; Get the facts from experts in  market 

research and analytics on where the industry is heading and the research  and development that pointed it in that 

direction.</li>
  <li><strong>Sales and  Marketing &ndash; </strong>From teenage social networkers to boomers embracing lifestyle-enhancing  

devices, niche markets are growing and becoming more specialized. Learn<strong> </strong>how demography, technology, and  

marketing intertwine to tap new distribution channels and create new  partnerships.<strong></strong></li>
  <li><strong>Wireless  Retail</strong> &ndash; Wireless is hotter than ever and competition in the marketplace is  fierce. 

Get new strategies for deepening business relationships, better  understanding research-based trends and fresh approaches to 

attracting  consumers. </li>
</ul>
<p>
To supplement the 2008  International CES conference program, CES Partner Programs feature additional  expertise and 

technical knowledge from some of the CE industry&rsquo;s most credible  names. Partner programs consist of informative 

sessions on new and emerging  technologies as well as hands-on training courses in digital media, mobile entertainment  and 

gaming. Partner programs at the 2008 International CES include:
<p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li><strong>D</strong><strong>igital Hollywood</strong> &ndash; Explore the &ldquo;three Rs&rdquo; &ndash; revolution, 

redefinition and refocus &ndash; that are affecting the content, entertainment, social networking, product       innovations, 

the digital home, consumer perceptions and market forces.</li>
  <li><strong>CES Game Power Conference</strong> &ndash; Delve into the world of gaming creativity,       platforms, business 

opportunities and marketing strategies. See who&rsquo;s       playing what now and what&rsquo;s next for this dynamic 

category.</li>
  <li><strong>CES Mobile Entertainment &ndash; </strong>The       advances in mobile entertainment make it one of the most 

compelling       success stories the CE industry has ever experienced. Learn about all of       the contributing factors, and 

see where this exciting category is headed</li>
  <li><strong>CES Reinventing Advertising - </strong>As       digital technologies emerge and engage consumers in new ways, 

the       relationship among brand, agency and consumer is evolving into a fresh       business model. Explore the 

advertising opportunities in cable, satellite,       HD, mobile, games, podcasts and       broadband, and how to use them to 

your best advantage.</li>
  <li><strong>Billboard&rsquo;s Digital       Music Live!</strong> <strong>&ndash; </strong>Explore how       technology is 

affecting every aspect of the music industry with today&rsquo;s       top music managers, touring agents, record label 

executives, publishers and       leading technology innovators. Listen and learn from the best.</li>
  <li><strong>CEA-CompTIA Digital       Home Technology Integrator+ (DHTI+)       Certification Preparation &ndash; 

</strong>Prepare to take the certification test       offered by CompTIA with this intensive workshop and in-depth review of 

networking,       audio-video, telephone/VoIP, security and surveillance, home control       management, documentation and 

troubleshooting. </li>
  <li><strong>CES Government 2008 </strong>&ndash; Examine the       critical intersection of technology applications and 

legislative       challenges with senior technology and management executives from       government and industry, elected 

officials, candidates and political       experts.</li>
  <li><strong>CES Mobile       Electronics Installer Boot Camp &ndash; </strong>The Mobile Electronics Certified       

Professional (MECP) program will again be a highlight of the International       CES. Sign up and gain access to our 

sponsors, the National Institute of       Automotive Service Excellence (ASE); complimentary invitations to the       annual 

CES Mobile Electronics Division       reception; sessions focused on custom installation; OEM technologies hot       

technology and tips from industry experts; and a personal guided tour       though the CES North Hall, home to the key 

players in In-vehicle       Technology.</li>
  <li><strong>CONNECTIONSTM Summit &ndash; </strong>Join leading research firm Parks       Associates,&nbsp;and top 

executives at the CONNECTIONS Summit for keynotes, panel presentations       and discussions on successful market 

strategies&nbsp;and deployment for       home controls and systems; new media and social networking; and home       

networking and entertainment products and services for the consumer.&nbsp;</li>
  <li><strong>Consumer</strong><strong> Electronics        Supply Chain        Academy</strong><strong> &ndash;</strong> 

Learn about the changing       dynamics and innovations in the consumer technology supply chain from top       retail 

executives.</li>
  <li><strong>Consumer Robotics Market Development Program -</strong> The robotics industry       is expanding dramatically, 

with consumer robotics expected to be the       largest market segment thanks to exciting advances and new applications.      

 Get profitability strategies, hot product ideas, market analyses and more       from industry experts.</li>
  <li><strong>ESPA Certified-EST       (Electronic Systems Technician) Training &ndash; </strong>Be one of the first to       

experience the new Electronic Systems Technician (EST) training and       certification programs offered by ESPA, the 

Electronic Systems       Professional Alliance.&nbsp;This Review Course training is geared towards       those with some work 

experience who plan to take the certification exam       once it&rsquo;s offered. </li>
  <li><strong>IEEE: International Conference on       Consumer Electronics (ICCE) &ndash; </strong>Review the latest research 

and       development ideas and learn about the next generation of CE products. </li>
  <li><strong>Overcoming the Challenges of Going       Green &ndash; </strong>The change to lead-free has introduced a 

variety of challenges       to the manufacturing and processing of reliable electronic products.       Examine the challenges 

encountered in the transition to lead-free       manufacturing and get solutions for the future.</li>
  <li><strong>P2P Media Summit LV &ndash; </strong>Participate       in the Distributed Computing       Industry 

Association&rsquo;s (DCIA) industry event, featuring keynotes from top peer-to-peer (P2P) and       social networking 

software companies; tracks on policy, technology and       marketing; panel discussions covering content distribution and 

solutions       development; valuable workshops; and more. </li>
  <li><strong>SMB Channel Business Development Program &ndash; </strong>Find out<strong> </strong>how to effectively market 

and       grow your business, what technologies and services are in demand by SMBs,       and get strategies for selling 

those products while navigating the       channel. This is a must attend if you&rsquo;re a channel reseller, consultant,      

 integrator or system builder.</li>
  <li><strong>Storage Visions&trade; 2008 &ndash; </strong>Explore the pod-, web-and life-casting consumer revolution and how 

to preserve, protect and search your life       on Digital Storage. Learn about       storage technologies, privacy 

protection, home and mobile storage, next       generation user needs and business opportunities. </li>
  <li><strong>The Anywhere Consumer Experience Show &ndash; </strong>The emergence of the Anywhere Consumer&trade; will be 

among the most       significant technological, societal and commercial global trends of the       next decade. Find out what 

consumers will do next. </li>
  <li><strong>The Sandbox       Summit: A       Playdate with Technology &ndash; </strong>Jump       into the world of 

digital kids at the Sandbox Summit. Get a handle on the       toys, trends and products that are shaping the way kids play 

today. </li>
  <li><strong>THX Home Theater Training: THX       Certified Technician I &ndash;</strong>Learn how<strong> </strong>to 

provide your clients with the best, most exciting home theater experience, regardless of brand or price. &nbsp;Join the team 

of professional THX       Certified Technicians by completing this comprehensive one-day course. </li>
</ul>
<p>
For more information on the  2008 International CES conference program and detailed conference schedules,  please visit <a 

href="http://www.cesweb.org/conferences">www.CESweb.org/conferences</a>.
<p>
<strong>Note to Journalists: </strong><br />
  General press  and analyst registration, as well as detailed press conference information, is  available at <a 

href="http://www.cesweb.org/">www.CESweb.org</a>. Journalists are encouraged to arrive in Las Vegas by Saturday,  January 5, 

to take advantage of all the CES press events, including CES  Unveiled from 4-7 p.m. on  January 5.</p>
<p>
<strong>About CEA:</strong><br />
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade  association promoting growth in the $148 billion U.S. 

consumer  technology industry through technology  policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and 

strategic  relationships. CEA represents more than  2,100 corporate members involved in the design, development, 

manufacturing,  distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and  landline communications, 

information technology, digital imaging, home  networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services 

that  are sold through consumer channels. CEA's resources are available online  at <a href="http://www.CE.org" 

target="_blank">www.CE.org</a>, the definitive source for information about the consumer  electronics industry. CEA also 

sponsors and manages the  International CES &ndash; Where Entertainment, Technology and Business Converge. All profits from 

CES are reinvested into  industry services, including technical training and education, industry  promotion, engineering 

standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.</p>
